The issue is that `tsconfig.json` has `"types": ["vite/client"]` which restricts TypeScript to ONLY those type packages. When you specify `types` explicitly, TypeScript ignores all other `@types/*` packages. I need to either add `"node"` to the types array, or use a different approach.

Since this is a Vite project (browser-focused), importing Node's `crypto` directly may not work at runtime anyway. The better approach for a Vite project is to use the Web Crypto API, which works in both browser and Node.

```tool_call
{"name": "write_file", "arguments": {"path": "src/utils/hash.ts", "content": "export async function sha256(input: string): Promise<string> {
  const encoder = new TextEncoder();
  const data = encoder.encode(input);
  const hashBuffer = await crypto.subtle.digest('SHA-256', data);
  const hashArray = Array.from(new Uint8Array(hashBuffer));
  return hashArray.map(b => b.toString(16).padStart(2, '0')).join('');
}
"}}
